OL,3,CLabour MPs overwhelmingly back Andy
OL,4,CBurnham for party leadership
OL,6,FAndy Burnham is almost guaranteed to
OL,7,Fbe the next prime minister of the
OL,8,FUnited Kingdom after 322 Labour MPs
OL,9,Fnominated him to take over from Sir
OL,10,FKeir Starmer.
OL,12,FThe total means that there are only 81
OL,13,FLabour MPs left who could nominate
OL,14,Fanother contender, the minimum needed
OL,15,Fto get on to the ballot.
OL,17,FBut convention dictates that the
OL,18,Foutgoing leader does not nominate a
OL,19,Fcandidate, meaning in reality there
OL,20,Fare no longer enough undeclared MPs to
OL,21,Fback an alternative to Mr Burnham.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
