CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1783653540
OL,3,CLabour MPs overwhelmingly back Andy
OL,4,CBurnham for party leadership
OL,6,FAlmost every member of the Cabinet
OL,7,Fbacked Mr Burnham, as did former
OL,8,Fhealth secretary Wes Streeting and
OL,9,Fformer armed forces minister Al Carns
OL,10,Fwho had previously been regarded as
OL,11,Fpotential challengers.
OL,13,FMr Streeting ruled himself out of
OL,14,Fcontention within minutes of Mr
OL,15,FBurnham announcing his candidacy
OL,16,Ffollowing Sir Keir's resignation on
OL,17,FJune 22, while Mr Carns said on
OL,18,FWednesday he would not put himself
OL,19,Fforward.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1783653540
OL,3,CLabour MPs overwhelmingly back Andy
OL,4,CBurnham for party leadership
OL,6,FKey Starmer ally Steve Reed was one of
OL,7,Fonly three Cabinet members who did not
OL,8,Fnominate Mr Burnham on Thursday, along
OL,9,Fwith Home Secretary Shabana Mahmood,
OL,10,Fwho has been spoken of as a potential
OL,11,Fchancellor, and party chairwoman Anna
OL,12,FTurley.
OL,14,FBut this does not necessarily mean
OL,15,Fthey do not support Mr Burnham, as
OL,16,Fnominations must be made in person or
OL,17,Fthrough a limited number of proxy
OL,18,Fvotes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1783653540
OL,3,CLabour MPs overwhelmingly back Andy
OL,4,CBurnham for party leadership
OL,6,FIt is also understood that Ms Mahmood,
OL,7,Fas chairwoman of the party's ruling
OL,8,Fnational executive committee, will not
OL,9,Fnominate a candidate.
OL,11,FMr Burnham will still need the support
OL,12,Fof three of Labour's affiliated
OL,13,Forganisations, including two trade
OL,14,Funions, to be formally nominated.
OL,16,FBut he is almost certain to secure the
OL,17,Frequired backing, with Usdaw general
OL,18,Fsecretary Joanne Thomas saying her
OL,19,Funion's executive committee had
OL,20,Falready unanimously decided to endorse
OL,21,Fhim.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
